does not store documents as DOS files, but rather it stores all
documents in a data file named "Forthscr.een" that it generates on
data disks.

This disk is intended to be used as a "booter". You place the disk in
your A: drive and turn on your computer. After the program loads, you
must switch to your data disk.

You can also launch EasyWriter 1.0 from DOS, by running its program
loader named "command.com" on the floppy disk. (Since you are working 
