patches described here to the boot disk:
http://www.os2museum.com/wp/installing-os2-1-x-in-a-virtualbox-vm/

To summarize, replace all occurrences of:
  B8 F4 01 BB C8 00 F7 E3 F7 F1
with
  B8 F4 01 BB C8 00 F7 E3 90 90

It currently will not install in PCem (or some real hardware
apparently) due to a known bug with OS/2''s FDISK. Unlike normal OS/2,
Citrix Multiuser''s setup will not let you skip that.

The CSD update disks must be installed from maintenance mode. To do
that, use the Citrix Multiuser OS/2 boot disk, and after install
starts from the second disk, hit escape.

A little more information can be found in this [Software Spotlight](https://winworldpc.com/winboards/viewtopic.php?t=8617).', '', 'OS2', null);
