INSERT INTO winworld.Releases (ReleaseUUID, ProductUUID, Name, VendorName, Slug, ReleaseOrder, ReleaseDate, EndOfLife, FuzzyDate, Arch, RAMRequirement, CPURequirement, DiskSpaceRequired, MultiUser, Networking, Type, SerialRequired, InstallInstructions, Notes, Platform, DefaultDownload) VALUES (0x1EF49EF3A12D11E9B7F9FA163E9022F0, 0x0C71676CA12D11E9B7F9FA163E9022F0, '1.00-1.01', '', '100', 0, '1987-05-01 10:00:00', null, 'True', null, 0, '286', 0, 'No', null, 'Text', 'False', '', 'May 1987 - SDK 1.00

1.00 includes a pre-release build of OS/2, Microsoft MASM and C 4.50 betas, and documentation for OS/2, Microsoft C, MASM, and OS/2 programming. 

The SDK also included (available here as a separate download) the [Microsoft Windows 1.04 SDK](/product/windows-sdk-ddk/windows-1x), [Windows 1.04](/product/windows-10/104), programming libraries, and [Microsoft C 4.0](/product/microsoft-c-c/40). Allegedly this was just to give developers an idea of how the OS/2 Presentation Manager would work. 

Wanted: Microsoft OS/2 SDK 1.00 Program Disk.  

August 1987 - SDK 1.01

1.01 consists of a single disk update, the OS/2 program disk, to the 1.00 set. 1.01 is only a minor change that adds a program selector. 1.01 also added pre-release documentation for "Windows Presentation Manager", although the software was not included until SDK 1.03. 

The 1.01 archive here contains the 1.01 program disk, as well as the May 1987 SDK 1.00 disks, but it is missing the 1.00 program disk (probably disk 1), and apparently another disk (disk 2, but it is not clear what should be on that disk). 

Wanted: Microsoft also released the Microsoft OS/2 DDK 1.00 at about the same time. 

Manuals can be found on Archive.org:
https://archive.org/details/os2-sdk-v1-1987', 'DOS,OS2', null);
INSERT INTO winworld.Releases (ReleaseUUID, ProductUUID, Name, VendorName, Slug, ReleaseOrder, ReleaseDate, EndOfLife, FuzzyDate, Arch, RAMRequirement, CPURequirement, DiskSpaceRequired, MultiUser, Networking, Type, SerialRequired, InstallInstructions, Notes, Platform, DefaultDownload) VALUES (0x05A1684DA13411E9B7F9FA163E9022F0, 0x0C71676CA12D11E9B7F9FA163E9022F0, '1.02', 'Microsoft', '102', 0, '1987-12-01 06:00:00', null, 'True', null, 0, '286', 0, 'No', null, 'GUI', 'False', '', 'December 1987 - SDK 1.02

Microsoft OS/2 SDK 1.02 includes:
- The final Microsoft OS/2 1.0
- MASM 5.00A
- Microsoft C Compiler 5.1 beta
- Almost complete tools, libraries, examples, and documentation.

According the pcjs site, this archive may be missing a "network"
disk, but the install can be completed by creating an empty disk.

There is more info about the 1.02 SDK here:
https://www.pcjs.org/disks/pcx86/tools/microsoft/os2/sdk/1.02/

Also see: 
http://web.archive.org/web/20150218015420/http://www.os2museum.com/wp
/os2-history/os2-beginnings/
', 'DOS,OS2', null);
INSERT INTO winworld.Releases (ReleaseUUID, ProductUUID, Name, VendorName, Slug, ReleaseOrder, ReleaseDate, EndOfLife, FuzzyDate, Arch, RAMRequirement, CPURequirement, DiskSpaceRequired, MultiUser, Networking, Type, SerialRequired, InstallInstructions, Notes, Platform, DefaultDownload) VALUES (0x93D8226BA13411E9B7F9FA163E9022F0, 0x0C71676CA12D11E9B7F9FA163E9022F0, '1.03', 'Microsoft', '103', 0, '1988-03-01 21:00:00', null, 'True', null, 0, '286', 0, 'No', null, 'GUI', 'False', '', 'March 1988 - SDK 1.03

The OS/2 SDK version 1.03 includes the first OS/2 1.1 pre-release kernel, the first public Presentation Manager builds, Microsoft C 5.1, MASM 5.1, The OS/2 Programmer''s Toolkit 1.0 (available here as a separate download), a draft copy of Charles
